-- Tesoro Plans to Flare Gases Tomorrow at Wilmington Refinery in California
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2010-12-30T09:25:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/tesoro-plans-to-flare-gases-tomorrow-at-wilmington-refinery-in-california.html
Tesoro Corp. , the largest
independent refiner in the Western U.S., plans to flare gases
tomorrow at its  Wilmington  plant in California, according to a
filing with state regulators.  The flaring isnâ€™t related to a breakdown, the  filing  with
the South Coast Air Quality Management District showed. Flaring,
the release of gases into the air, is a safety measure that
prevents excess pressure from building up when processing units
are stopping or starting.  Tesoro was scheduled to flare from yesterday to today,
according to a Dec. 28 filing with the regulator. The San
Antonio-based company planned to start a unit following
maintenance, it said the same day.  The refinery has capacity to process about 104,000 barrels
of oil a day, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
